{"commands": [{"bindings": {}, "collapsed": false, "command": "\n%md-sandbox\n\n<div style=\"text-align: center; line-height: 0; padding-top: 9px;\">\n  <img src=\"https://databricks.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/db-academy-rgb-1200px.png\" alt=\"Databricks Learning\" style=\"width: 1200px\">\n</div>", "commandTitle": "", "commandType": "auto", "commandVersion": 0, "commentThread": [], "commentsVisible": false, "customPlotOptions": {}, "datasetPreviewNameToCmdIdMap": {}, "diffDeletes": [], "diffInserts": [], "displayType": "table", "error": null, "errorSummary": null, "finishTime": 0, "globalVars": {}, "guid": "4031ef21-f1ee-4fcb-84f7-a814eb71536f", "height": "auto", "hideCommandCode": false, "hideCommandResult": false, "iPythonMetadata": null, "inputWidgets": {}, "latestUser": "", "latestUserId": null, "nuid": "c91f6c10-89eb-44ee-a854-77ea1caa26ba", "origId": 0, "parentHierarchy": [], "pivotAggregation": null, "pivotColumns": null, "position": 1, "results": null, "showCommandTitle": false, "startTime": 0, "state": "finished", "streamStates": {}, "submitTime": 0, "subtype": "command", "version": "CommandV1", "width": "auto", "workflows": [], "xColumns": null, "yColumns": null}, {"bindings": {}, "collapsed": false, "command": "%md-sandbox\n<img src=\"https://files.training.databricks.com/images/Apache-Spark-Logo_TM_200px.png\" style=\"float: left: margin: 20px\"/>\n\n# Source To Bronze - Macro Data\n\nWe also process external data to support our decision making. One of our sources is the Macroeconomic Data with no connection to our internal datasets: we receive this data every month from the central bank, containing macro economic indicators such as unemployment and GDP. It helps us build a single decimal metric, which is used to update investors' credit scores. These credit scores serve as a baseline for approving or denying loan requests. \n\nCreate a Delta table from the Macro Data CSV. Define the schema and write the DataFrame to the specified directory.\n\n## In this exercise you will:\n* Learn to define a CSV schema manually\n\n## Prerequisites\n* Web browser: **Chrome**\n* A cluster configured with **8 cores** and **DBR 7.0**", "commandTitle": "", "commandType": "auto", "commandVersion": 0, "commentThread": [], "commentsVisible": false, "customPlotOptions": {}, "datasetPreviewNameToCmdIdMap": {}, "diffDeletes": [], "diffInserts": [], "displayType": "table", "error": null, "errorSummary": null, "finishTime": 0, "globalVars": {}, "guid": "92f36154-7b31-4d1d-9cd4-00a9d513b568", "height": "auto", "hideCommandCode": false, "hideCommandResult": false, "iPythonMetadata": null, "inputWidgets": {}, "latestUser": "", "latestUserId": null, "nuid": "a99e4954-d034-4d2e-a9b0-dd8bf72f6289", "origId": 0, "parentHierarchy": [], "pivotAggregation": null, "pivotColumns": null, "position": 2, "results": null, "showCommandTitle": false, "startTime": 0, "state": "finished", "streamStates": {}, "submitTime": 0, "subtype": "command", "version": "CommandV1", "width": "auto", "workflows": [], "xColumns": null, "yColumns": null}, {"bindings": {}, "collapsed": false, "command": "%md-sandbox\n<h2 style=\"color:red\">Instructor Note</h2>\n\n\n\nThings to talk about:\n- this is the last bronze table\n- using 3rd party data to update our metrics is common practice\n- what are the benefits of importing such data into our data lake\n- talk about the different schema defining options, including DDL", "commandTitle": "", "commandType": "auto", "commandVersion": 0, "commentThread": [], "commentsVisible": false, "customPlotOptions": {}, "datasetPreviewNameToCmdIdMap": {}, "diffDeletes": [], "diffInserts": [], "displayType": "table", "error": null, "errorSummary": null, "finishTime": 0, "globalVars": {}, "guid": "13afa8cf-d88d-42f8-ada9-cfddcaef39f3", "height": "auto", "hideCommandCode": false, "hideCommandResult": false, "iPythonMetadata": null, "inputWidgets": {}, "latestUser": "", "latestUserId": null, "nuid": "9b4e3ad0-b1d6-429e-8af9-081d8f865ac3", "origId": 0, "parentHierarchy": [], "pivotAggregation": null, "pivotColumns": null, "position": 3, "results": null, "showCommandTitle": false, "startTime": 0, "state": "finished", "streamStates": {}, "submitTime": 0, "subtype": "command", "version": "CommandV1", "width": "auto", "workflows": [], "xColumns": null, "yColumns": null}, {"bindings": {}, "collapsed": false, "command": "%md\n## ![Spark Logo Tiny](https://files.training.databricks.com/images/105/logo_spark_tiny.png) Classroom-Setup<br>\n\nFor each lesson to execute correctly, please make sure to run the **`Classroom-Setup`** cell at the start of each lesson (see the next cell) and the **`Classroom-Cleanup`** cell at the end of each lesson.", "commandTitle": "", "commandType": "auto", "commandVersion": 0, "commentThread": [], "commentsVisible": false, "customPlotOptions": {}, "datasetPreviewNameToCmdIdMap": {}, "diffDeletes": [], "diffInserts": [], "displayType": "table", "error": null, "errorSummary": null, "finishTime": 0, "globalVars": {}, "guid": "da7ce739-7261-41b4-9da9-20d82294e16e", "height": "auto", "hideCommandCode": false, "hideCommandResult": false, "iPythonMetadata": null, "inputWidgets": {}, "latestUser": "", "latestUserId": null, "nuid": "45e9d36a-4c25-4ced-bc95-ed62a06d4bb1", "origId": 0, "parentHierarchy": [], "pivotAggregation": null, "pivotColumns": null, "position": 4, "results": null, "showCommandTitle": false, "startTime": 0, "state": "finished", "streamStates": {}, "submitTime": 0, "subtype": "command", "version": "CommandV1", "width": "auto", "workflows": [], "xColumns": null, "yColumns": null}, {"bindings": {}, "collapsed": false, "command": "%run ./Includes/PCF-06B-ClassroomSetup", "commandTitle": "", "commandType": "auto", "commandVersion": 0, "commentThread": [], "commentsVisible": false, "customPlotOptions": {}, "datasetPreviewNameToCmdIdMap": {}, "diffDeletes": [], "diffInserts": [], "displayType": "table", "error": null, "errorSummary": null, "finishTime": 0, "globalVars": {}, "guid": "8eca75d6-a188-4291-8354-fc5d4543604b", "height": "auto", "hideCommandCode": false, "hideCommandResult": false, "iPythonMetadata": null, "inputWidgets": {}, "latestUser": "", "latestUserId": null, "nuid": "72d10ed5-8863-45cc-853b-94d56f5b3bc5", "origId": 0, "parentHierarchy": [], "pivotAggregation": null, "pivotColumns": null, "position": 5, "results": null, "showCommandTitle": false, "startTime": 0, "state": "finished", "streamStates": {}, "submitTime": 0, "subtype": "command", "version": "CommandV1", "width": "auto", "workflows": [], "xColumns": null, "yColumns": null}, {"bindings": {}, "collapsed": false, "command": "%md\n## ![Spark Logo Tiny](https://files.training.databricks.com/images/105/logo_spark_tiny.png) Steps to Complete\nImplement the function **`challenge()`** to achieve the following:\n- Explore the schema of the CSV file: use the **`%fs head`** command in a new cell. <a href=\"https://docs.databricks.com/dev-tools/databricks-utils.html#dbutils-fs\" target=\"_blank\">Documentation</a>\n- Read the Suppliers CSV file from the **`macroDataPath`** into a DataFrame.\n- Define the schema according to the table below this cell.\n- Write the resulting DataFrame as a Delta table to **`targetDirectory`**.\n- Return the final DataFrame, which should have the following schema:\n\n|name|type|\n|---|---|\n|date|DateType|\n|fedfunds|DoubleType|\n|gdp|FloatType|\n|bamlh0a0hym2|FloatType|\n|gfdegdq188s|FloatType|\n|indpro|FloatType|\n|a191rl1q225sbea|FloatType|\n|indgs10dpro|FloatType|\n|unrate|FloatType|\n|dexuseu|FloatType|", "commandTitle": "", "commandType": "auto", "commandVersion": 0, "commentThread": [], "commentsVisible": false, "customPlotOptions": {}, "datasetPreviewNameToCmdIdMap": {}, "diffDeletes": [], "diffInserts": [], "displayType": "table", "error": null, "errorSummary": null, "finishTime": 0, "globalVars": {}, "guid": "e20703fe-d9ff-4d5c-9c1e-8339925faa98", "height": "auto", "hideCommandCode": false, "hideCommandResult": false, "iPythonMetadata": null, "inputWidgets": {}, "latestUser": "", "latestUserId": null, "nuid": "97c78782-e020-40b2-bc14-9016cf5c3a35", "origId": 0, "parentHierarchy": [], "pivotAggregation": null, "pivotColumns": null, "position": 6, "results": null, "showCommandTitle": false, "startTime": 0, "state": "finished", "streamStates": {}, "submitTime": 0, "subtype": "command", "version": "CommandV1", "width": "auto", "workflows": [], "xColumns": null, "yColumns": null}, {"bindings": {}, "collapsed": false, "command": "// ANSWER\n\ndef solution(spark:org.apache.spark.sql.SparkSession, macroDataPath:String, targetDirectory:String) : DataFrame = {\n  import org.apache.spark.sql.types._\n  import org.apache.spark.sql.functions._\n\n  // Define the schema according to \"Steps to Complete\".\n    val macroSchema = \"date DATE, fedfunds DOUBLE, gdp FLOAT, bamlh0a0hym2 FLOAT, gfdegdq188s FLOAT, indpro FLOAT, a191rl1q225sbea FLOAT, dgs10 FLOAT, unrate FLOAT, dexuseu FLOAT\"\n  \n  // Read macroDataPath and make sure that:\n  // the first row is the header and\n  // the correct delimiter is specified.\n    val df = (spark.read\n          .schema(macroSchema)\n          .option(\"header\", true)\n          .option(\"delimiter\", \";\")\n          .csv(macroDataPath)\n         )\n \n  // Write the final DataFrame as a Delta table to targetDirectory.\n    // Make sure you let Spark overwrite the target location if necessary.\n  df.write.mode(\"overwrite\").option(\"overwriteSchema\", \"true\").format(\"delta\").save(targetDirectory)  \n  \n  // Return the final DataFrame.\n  return df\n}\n\nval finalDF = solution(spark, macroDataPath, targetDirectory)\ndisplay(finalDF)", "commandTitle": "", "commandType": "auto", "commandVersion": 0, "commentThread": [], "commentsVisible": false, "customPlotOptions": {}, "datasetPreviewNameToCmdIdMap": {}, "diffDeletes": [], "diffInserts": [], "displayType": "table", "error": null, "errorSummary": null, "finishTime": 0, "globalVars": {}, "guid": "8d90e08c-0ac7-45ef-8fbc-43